Roughly chop the @mushrooms{250%g}.

Trim and thinly slice the @scallion{1}.

Place a large pan over high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, fry the @Irish beef strips{250%g} until browned, shifting as they 
colour, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Once seared, remove from the pan and set aside.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Meat is safe to 
> eat when the outside is browned.

> TIP: You don't want to overcrowd the pan—cook in batches if necessary!

Return the pan (no need to wipe) to high heat with another drizzle of oil.

When hot, add the mushrooms and season with salt and pepper.

Fry until softened, stirring occasionally, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Lower the heat to medium-high and add the @creme fraiche{110%g}, 
@paprika{2%sachet(s)}, @Worcester sauce{1%sachet(s)}, @beef stock{1%sachet(s)} and 
half the scallion to the pan.

Stir in @water{75%ml} (double for 4p) and leave to simmer until slightly 
thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add the beef strips and stir to warm through and coat with the sauce.

Carefully separate the @udon noodles{300%g} by hand then add to the pan and 
gently toss in the sauce until softened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Season to taste with salt and pepper. Add a splash of @water{to taste} to 
loosen the sauce if necessary.

> Little Chef's TIP: Kids can help with separating the noodles.

Divide the beef stroganoff noodles between bowls.

Garnish with a sprinkling of the remaining scallion.